&lt;li&gt;Assist in the integration of sensor data and firmware feedback into the core control loops.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help implement and validate mathematical models used for robot limb positioning and movement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the software interfaces that translate high-level behavioral goals into executable robot tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather and analyze performance data from both physical hardware and simulation environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write unit tests and maintain clear documentation for software features to ensure system stability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in team code reviews and contribute to a collaborative, agile development process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent and lead with Apptronik&#39;s core values: CHIPC - Curiosity, Humility, Integrity, Passion, Creativity.&lt;/li&gt;
